CCS : Cascading Style Sheets

Why CSS :
Provides the overall look of the web page 
Allow us to remove presentational infomation from the HTML

CSS Spec :
CSS1 : 1996  -> Fonts,colors,Alignment, Spacing
CSS2.1 : 2004 -> Layout, position
CSS3 : Inprogress -> Effects,sizing

Selectors and Property Value  :
Selectors is a pattern used to apply styles to element.

Types of selector :
1)element selector
body{ 
		backgroung-color : #00000;
	}

2)ID selector:
#menu {
	backgroung-color : #00000;
}

3)Class selector
.abc{
	backgroung-color : #00000;
}
Body is a selector where we want to apply the effect
PropertyName:value -> assigned property with the defined value


Types of CSS :
Inline  : <h1 style="color:blue;margin-left:30px;">This is a heading</h1>

Internal
<head>
<style>
body {
    background-color: linen;
}

h1 {
    color: maroon;
    margin-left: 40px;
} 
</style>
</head>

External 

HTML :<head>
<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="mystyle.css">
</head>


An inline style (inside a specific HTML element) has the highest priority, which means that it will override a style defined inside the <head> tag, or in an external style sheet, or a browser default value.


